Full Title: Cognitive Processes in Language=20
Short Title: CogLang=20

Date: 25-May-2010 - 27-May-2010
Location: ?=F3d?, Poland=20
Contact Person: Janusz Badio
Meeting Email: coglang@uni.lodz.pl

Linguistic Field(s): Cognitive Science=20

Call Deadline: 31-Dec-2009=20

Meeting Description:

The Department of English and General Linguistics at University of ?=F3d?
announces the International Conference on Cognitive Processes in Language.
The aim of the Conference is to provide a forum for  discussion of issues
in cognition, psychology and language.=20

The following scholars have accepted our invitation to address the
conference as plenary speakers:
=20
Alan Cienki (Free University of Amsterdam)
Roman Kalisz (University of Gda?sk)=20

Call for Papers:

We invite papers in the following areas of research:

- Attention in language
- Memory in language=20
- Concept formation in language
- Construal of meaning
- Categorization processes in language
- Framing
- Imagery in language
- Figurative processes in language
- Language and embodiment
- Problem solving as a linguistic phenomenon
- Simulation semantics
- Gesturing, sign languages
- Planning and inferencing in discourse comprehension
- Mental processes in consecutive translation
- Mental lexicon
- Cognitive processes in language acquisition
- Conceptual chunking/segmentation in language
- Cognitive processing and language deficits (aphasia,  dyslexia, etc)
- Mental representations=20
- Cognitive processes in 2nd language learning

This list is not exhaustive. =20

Individual papers should take 20 minutes, followed by 10 minutes for
discussion. Deadline for submission of abstracts (max. 500 words) is
December 31st 2009. All participants must register by filling out the
Registration Form (the address to be announced later). Do not hesitate to
contact us at jbadio@uni.lodz.pl  if you encounter any problems.

Cost and Payment Information:

The conference fee (early) is 120 EUR (70 EUR for Ph.D. students), late
payments (140 EUR, 90 EUR for Ph. D. students) It covers the cost of
participation, conference materials, lunches at the conference venue, gala
dinner and social programme.=20

