From Warsaw:
=20
Warsaw Frederick Chopin Airport is connected to "Warszawa Centralna"
Railway Station (Warsaw Central Railway Station) by a municipal bus line
and taxis. Bus line 175 runs all week from 04:50 to 23:00. The ride takes
approx. 25 minutes. The bus ticket (valid 40 minutes) can be purchased in
the Arrivals Hall. The price is 2, 80 PLN. Three taxi corporations offer
services from the airport to the railway station: Merc Taxi, MPT Radio
Taxi, Sawa Taxi. The ride costs about 40 PLN. Other non-corporate taxi
services are not recommended! Trains from Warsaw Central Railway Station
leave at 20 minutes past every hour. The last departure on working days is
at 9.20 p.m.; less frequently on weekends. Tickets can be purchased in the
main hall of the Station. 2nd class ticket costs 31 PLN, and the journey
takes 90 minutes. Trains arrive at ?=F3d? Fabryczna Railway Station.There a=
re
also direct coach connections from the Warsaw airport to ?=F3d? Central Coa=
ch
Station. The buses leave at 00:25, 11:00, 13:00, 14:30, 16:30, 17:30,
19:45, and 22:10. The journey takes about 2 hours and 15 minutes. Tickets
can be purchased from the coach driver at about 30 PLN. ?=F3d? Central Coac=
h
Station is adjacent to the ?=F3d? Fabryczna Railway Station - both stations
are located in the same building. International buses arrive at ?=F3d?
Central Coach Station.=20

In ?=F3d?:
